description:
Speaking The Truth In Love To Muslims | Full Movie

How do I approach Muslims with the gospel? How are Islam and Christianity different? How do Muslims view the Bible and Christ? If you've asked yourself any of these questions, this insightful book will provide the answers.

Through reading Speaking the Truth in Love to Muslims, you will learn more about their history and religion and how to witness to them. This book provides a concise summary of the Lutheran law and gospel approach to Islam. This is a great resource for personal or group Bible study. Questions are also included for discussion.

This DVD Bible study is designed to encourage Christians to understand Islam, become acquainted with their Muslim neighbors, and discover why Muslims still need the gospel of Christ. Islam and the view of Muslims are two powerfully contending topics. They are frequently in the news, and the coverage is often alarming. Anything poorly understood can generate negative emotions or fears that discourage contact with Muslim people. What repercussions does this kind of coverage have on Christians?  By contrast, the Scriptures give Christ’s Church an uncommon attitude toward these types of religious backgrounds. Jesus includes everyone in the scope of the Great Commission. Men and women who are convinced of this can overcome the challenges raised by their fears and begin to build positive kingdom-building relationships with Muslims. Geared for Group Discussion, the four lessons on this DVD include: Lesson 1: Introduction - Basics
Lesson 2: God’s Nature – Who is God?
Lesson 3: Muslim Beliefs/Practices
Lesson 4: Reaching Out
